title: Despite loss, Navy receives votes in both football polls
text:
var ssaUrl = ('https:' == document.location.protocol ? 'https://' : 'http://') + 'pixel.sitescout.com/iap/0ea84626951144d2';new Image().src = ssaUrl;"/> College Football Despite loss, Navy receives votes in both football polls 
Navy played Notre Dame on Saturday in South Bend, Indiana. Mids off until Oct. 24 against Tulane 
The Navy football team received votes in both the Associated Press and USA Today/Coaches poll a day after the Mids battled No. 15 Notre Dame in South Bend before falling, 41-24. 
The Mids received three voting points in the Associated Press poll and two voting points in the USA Today/Coaches poll. 
Navy is off to a 4-1 start for the first time since 2006 and will have a bye this week before playing six-consecutive games against foes from the American Athletic Conference starting with Homecoming at Navy-Marine Corps Memorial Stadium on Oct. 24 against Tulane at 1 p.m. Navy is currently 2-0 in the American and tied with Memphis and Houston for first place.
